The paper discusses the application of bibliometric analysis methods to the work of a researcher in the field of scientometrics, which is a subfield of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the analysis of citation networks and the distribution of publication years of cited references, which are relevant to the sub-categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of algorithmic historiography, which is relevant to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and the analysis of bibliographic domains, which is relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CY).
